  "name": "Strait of Hormuz — SEAD + Strike Package",
  "description": "A multi-phase blue air/naval package contests the Strait of Hormuz across three loosely-separated engagements: SEAD fighters ingress first to suppress central coastal SAM sites; CAP fighters screen the center against red interceptors; and strike fighters hold offshore, then push northwest to attack a red frigate sheltered in a western naval pocket with its escorts. An ISR UAV (weapons-hold) maintains the air picture while a blue command ship stands off to the south. Exercises multi-waypoint routing, phased starts (via initial-waypoint holds), mixed ROE, detection, engagement, kill chains, MOEs, and playback.",
